# Testing rules
- Follow test pyramid: many unit tests, fewer integration tests, very selective E2E tests.
- Add tests in the same step as implementation, not later.
- For Python services use pytest.
- For FastAPI routes use TestClient or async HTTPX tests as appropriate.
- Integration tests must run against Dockerized dependencies when persistence or network boundaries matter.
- E2E tests must verify real workflows across service boundaries.
- Do not merge a new service contract without tests covering success, failure, and edge cases.
- Keep fixtures reusable and deterministic.
- Use factories for sample tickers, bars, and screening rules.